            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "٣. وَقَالَ (عليه السلام): الْبُخْلُ عَارٌ وَالْجُبْنُ مَنْقَصَةٌ وَالْفَقْرُ يُخْرِسُ الْفَطِنَ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " عَنْ "
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "حُجَّتِهِ وَالْمُقِلُّ غَرِيبٌ"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " فِي"
            }
          ]
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:3:276:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/3/3",
        "text": [
          " بَلْدَتِهِ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "3. Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him, said: Miserliness is shame; cowardice is a defect; poverty disables an intelligent man from arguing his case; and a destitute person is a stranger in his home town."
          ]
        }
      }
